#!/bin/bash
# Gate hook: enforces codebase-memory-mcp-FIRST for code discovery.
# First Grep/Glob/Read/Search per session -> BLOCK (exit 2) with guidance.
# The marker is written on that blocking call, so the immediate retry AND every
# later call in the session proceed (exit 0). One speed-bump per session, not a wall.
# PPID = Claude Code process PID, unique per session.
GATE=/tmp/cbm-code-discovery-gate-$PPID
find /tmp -name 'cbm-code-discovery-gate-*' -mtime +1 -delete 2>/dev/null
if [ -f "$GATE" ]; then
    exit 0
fi
touch "$GATE"
cat >&2 <<'MSG'
BLOCKED once this session: try codebase-memory-mcp FIRST for code discovery.
  search_graph(query="..." | name_pattern=".*X.*")  -> find functions/classes/components
  trace_path(function_name="X", direction="both")    -> callers/callees, impact analysis
  get_code_snippet(qualified_name="...")              -> read a symbol's source
Then Grep/Glob/Read are unblocked for the rest of the session -- just retry your call.
If this repo's graph is empty (search_graph returns nothing), retry to proceed with
Grep/Read, or run index_repository once to populate it.
MSG
exit 2
